Confluence will work with almost any JDBC supported databases.  Even ones that don't support foreign keys or proper transaction isolation.

If Confluence has been running on a database for some time that doesn't support proper transaction isolation, data can be corrupted.  In most cases Confluence will run perfectly fine until a backup or upgrade is attempted.  Usually this will fail because related data isn't available (because Confluence relies on the database foreign key constraints).

It would be nice to have a utility built in to Confluence that manually verifies the relationships and optionally deletes orphaned data.

