The same is true when I use a count=true jiraissue macro to show the number of issues; this is linked, users expect it to go to a nice familiar html list of issues, but are instead assaulted with "yucky" xml.

I can understand wanting the xml, as it's handy for those of us into feed readers, but for most of my users it's not useful. So if we could have a parameter that lets us specify a link to the issue navigator, it would be very handy.

