How to use SetContentPermission method from the SOAP APIs?

I have Confluence 2.7.3 installed.
How do you use the SetContentPermission (Session ID, Page ID, "View" or "Edit", Group/People colection) method from the SOAP APIs? What I would like to do is to assign "view" or "edit" permissions on a page for a set of people or groups.

There seems to be limited documentation on the Confluence website. I tried different approaches to use the SetContentPermission method using various parameters but it doesn't seem to work. It seems like on JIRA messageboard other developers using SetContentPermission from the SOAP APIs are having difficulty as well.

I've provide a sample of how I was using the setContentPermission method (.NET C#) to set view only restrictions on a page for the "test group".

// create confluence service
ConfluenceSoapServiceService service = new ConfluenceSoapServiceService();

// create collection for group/people to assign to the page
RemoteContentPermission[] objGroupCollection = new RemoteContentPermission[1];

// instantiate a group ("test user" group)
RemoteContentPermission objGroup = new RemoteContentPermission();
objGroup.groupName = "test user";

// put the "test user" group in the collection
objGroupCollection[0] = objGroup;

// assign the group collection to view only permissions 
// the selected page
bool flag = service.setContentPermissions(pageTN.Profile.SessionId, remotePage.id, "VIEW", objGroupCollection);

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
